    <p>The connectors 无论...都 and 不管...都 are nearly interchangeable in meaning, but 无论 is slightly more formal and preferred in writing, while 不管 is more common in speech. Both express that the result stays the same regardless of the condition. They can be followed by question words like 谁 (who), 什么 (what), 哪里 (where), or 怎么 (how) to create powerful universal statements: 无论你去哪里，我都跟着你。(No matter where you go, I will follow you.)</p>

    <p>The pair 不是...而是 is particularly useful for correcting misunderstandings or clarifying your position. It directly negates one interpretation and replaces it with another: 我不是不想帮你，而是真的没有办法。(It is not that I do not want to help you, but rather that I truly have no way to.) This pattern appears frequently in debates, explanations, and persuasive writing.</p>

